<subSubSection id="C33CA9C7FFA6FFD1AF91FD87BB5AC1DA" pageId="2" pageNumber="367" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="8B99FA4CFFA6FFD1AF91FD87BC9AC090" blockId="2.[723,1315,603,1026]" pageId="2" pageNumber="367">
<emphasis id="B952265EFFA6FFD1AF91FD87BC66C02E" bold="true" box="[723,878,603,632]" pageId="2" pageNumber="367">Taxonomy.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C2681CFFFA6FFD1AED1FD87BC76C0F6" authorityName="Peters" authorityYear="1846" class="Mammalia" family="Bathyergidae" genus="Heliophobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="2" pageNumber="367" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="argenteocinereus">Heliophobius argenteocinereus Peters, 1846</taxonomicName>
, 
<materialsCitation id="3B4EF011FFA6FFD1AECFFD5FBC86C090" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3785200316" pageId="2" pageNumber="367">Tete (on the Zambezi River), Mozambique</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B99FA4CFFA6FFD1AF97FD12BB5AC1DA" blockId="2.[723,1315,603,1026]" pageId="2" pageNumber="367">
Based on the phylogeographic study by C. G. Faulkes and colleagues in 2011, it is very likely that the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C2681CFFFA6FFD1A93DFCFCBA2BC16B" authorityName="Peters" authorityYear="1846" box="[1151,1315,800,829]" class="Mammalia" family="Bathyergidae" genus="Heliophobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="2" pageNumber="367" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Heliophobius</taxonomicName>
is represented by more than one species. Five subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
